docs.abstract: Apple, Facebook, Amazon and Alphabet will post quarterly earnings this week, reflecting how they are doing in online ads, mobile and cloud computing.
docs.snippet: Apple, Facebook, Amazon and Alphabet will post quarterly earnings this week, reflecting how they are doing in online ads, mobile and cloud computing.
docs.lead_paragraph: This week will offer a glimpse into just how dominant some of the world’s biggest technology companies have become.

docs.abstract: Analysts say the global cloud-computing business will be worth $67 billion by 2020. Amazon and Microsoft are the current leaders in the industry.

docs.lead_paragraph: The world of enterprise software and computing is not sexy — in fact, the mere mention of it may put you to sleep. But if you’re still with me, there’s been plenty of action in that world lately.

docs.abstract: Amazon reported net income of $857 million, the second quarter in a row it has shown a record profit even as it invests heavily in its own growth.

docs.lead_paragraph: SEATTLE — For most of its life, Amazon sacrificed profits if it could build another few warehouses to ship orders to customers more quickly or find some other investment to fuel its growth.

headline.main: Amazon’s Profits Grow More Than 800 Percent, Lifted by Cloud Services

headline.main: Forget Beanbag Chairs. Amazon Is Giving Its Workers Treehouses.
